{
  "doc_id": "15681",
  "text": "Work interfering with family was also hypothesized to have a negative association with both types of social support. As shown in Figure 2 , these expected relationships were upheld, work interfering with family was negatively related to both emotional sustenance from family, β = −.29, t(143) = −3.77, p < .01, and instrumental assistance from family, β = −.29, t(143) = −3.65, p < .01. This finding is consistent with the suggestion that families may find it difficult to provide social support to workers when the demands of the worker's job interfere with the demands of the worker's family [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
